tibble(line_no = seq(lines), line = lines) %>%

create_text_df <- function(text) {
  tibble(line_no = seq(text), line = text) %>%
    unnest_tokens(output = word, input = line)
}
create_text_df

TF IDF

term frequency - inverse document frequency


library(tidytext)

unnest_tokens(token = )

  "This is a sentence about cats.",

Error in UseMethod("pull") : 
  no applicable method for 'pull' applied to an object of class "function"

TF = Term Frequency will be high for important words(in a doc)

DF = document frequency will be low if it is in few documents

IDF = Inverse Document Frequency 1/DF

TF-IDF = Term Frequency - Inverse Document Frequency is a measure of how important a word is to a document in a collection of documents

TF = log(ntimes term in document / n terms in document) DF = log(n of documents term appears in / n documents) tf-idf = TF*log(1/df)

Lesson 3

N-grams

bigrams = words of two (e.g.the who, may the, the queen)

trigrams = words of three (e.g.may the force)

phrases <- c(
  "here is some text",
  "again more text",
  "text is text"
)

phrases_df <- tibble(
  phrase = phrases,
  id     = 1:3
) 


phrases_df %>%
  unnest_tokens(bigram, phrase, token = "ngrams", n = 2)

For the book P&P, find the top bigrams and trigrams

book_df <- tibble(
  id = 1:length(prideprejudice),
  text = prideprejudice
)

book_df %>%
  unnest_tokens(bigram, text, token = "ngrams", n = 2) %>%
  count(bigram, sort = TRUE)
book_df %>%
  unnest_tokens(trigram, text, token = "ngrams", n = 3) %>%
  count(trigram, sort = TRUE)
book_df %>%
  unnest_tokens(character, text, token = "characters") %>%
  count(character, sort = TRUE)
